message.reasoning_content:
The user is asking me to respond to a survey about AI in education as if I were an Australian school teacher. I need to provide responses to 10 statements about AI in education using the response options: 'Strongly disagree', 'Disagree', 'Agree', 'Strongly agree', 'I don't know'.

Let me think through each statement and provide thoughtful, balanced responses as a teacher would:

[TT4G35A]: AI helps teachers write or improve lesson plans - AGREE (AI can definitely assist with this)

[TT4G35B]: AI enables teachers to adapt learning material to different students' abilities - AGREE (AI has good potential for personalization)

[TT4G35C]: AI assists teachers in supporting students individually - AGREE (AI tools can provide individual support)

[TT4G35D]: AI supports students with specific needs - AGREE (AI can be beneficial for multilingual learners and SEN support)

[TT4G35E]: AI helps teachers automate administrative tasks - STRONGLY AGREE (This is a clear benefit of AI)

[TT4G35F]: AI enables students to misrepresent others' work as their own - AGREE (This is a legitimate concern - AI can be used for plagiarism)

[TT4G35G]: AI makes recommendations that may not be appropriate or correct - AGREE (This is a real concern)

[TT4G35H]: AI amplifies biases that reinforce students' misconceptions - AGREE (This is a documented issue with AI)

[TT4G35I]: AI jeopardises the privacy and security of student data - AGREE (This is a legitimate concern)

[TT4G35J]: AI suggests unsuitable pedagogical approaches that teachers would use with students - AGREE (AI doesn't always understand educational best practices)

I should provide a balanced perspective that recognizes both benefits and concerns with AI in education.
